  "body": "Try It Now  What percent of the data in a normal distribution has z-score below ?  This is a negative z-score, and we want the percentage of values greater than it, so we need to subtract the value for z = +0.23 from 1: . 40.9% percent of the data in a normal distribution have z-scores less than -0.23.  "
